---
// Static landing / about page. Lives at /about. Pure Astro, no
// client JS — the page is the same on first paint as fully loaded.
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Folio is a constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature. Built for authors and speech-language pathologists. Runs in your browser, never sends your manuscript anywhere."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://folio.harmonic-systems.org/about" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Folio" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Folio — about" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="A constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature. Built for authors and speech-language pathologists." />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://folio.harmonic-systems.org/about" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Folio — about" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="A constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature." />
    <script
      is:inline
      defer
      data-domain="folio.harmonic-systems.org"
      src="https://plausible.io/js/script.js"
    ></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <!-- Async font CSS: don't block first paint on a third-party
         stylesheet; Georgia renders immediately, Caslon swaps in. -->
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Caslon+Text:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap"
      media="print"
      onload="this.media='all'"
    />
    <noscript>
      <link
        rel="stylesheet"
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Caslon+Text:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap"
      />
    </noscript>
    <title>Folio — about</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: only light; /* 'only' opts out of Chrome Android Auto Dark; bare 'light' would not */
        --cream: #f7f1e6;
        --beige: #ece2cf;
        --taupe: #8a7c66;
        --ink: #2c2620;
        --rule: #d9cdb4;
        --ochre: #a37828;
        --rust: #9a4a2a;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0; padding: 0;
        background: var(--cream); color: var(--ink);
        font-family: 'Libre Caslon Text', Georgia, serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      main {
        max-width: 44rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem;
      }
      header.hero { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
      h1 {
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      }
      .tagline {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--taupe);
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
      }
      .cta-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
      }
      .cta {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 3px;
        border: 1px solid transparent;
      }
      .cta.primary {
        background: var(--ink);
        color: var(--cream);
        border-color: var(--ink);
      }
      .cta.primary:hover { background: #1a1612; }
      .cta.secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--ink);
        border-color: var(--rule);
      }
      .cta.secondary:hover { background: var(--surface, #fff); border-color: var(--taupe); }

      section { margin: 3rem 0; }
      h2 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.005em;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--taupe);
        margin: 2rem 0 0.5rem;
      }
      p { margin: 0 0 1.1rem; font-size: 1.02rem; }

      ul.audience, ul.features, ul.upcoming {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      }
      ul.audience li {
        padding: 1rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      }
      ul.audience li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.audience strong {
        display: block;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--ochre);
        margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
      }

      ul.features {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1rem 1.5rem;
      }
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        ul.features { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }
      ul.features li {
        padding: 1rem;
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      ul.features strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      ul.features span { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--taupe); line-height: 1.5; }

      ul.upcoming li {
        padding: 0.5rem 0;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: var(--taupe);
        font-style: italic;
        border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--rule);
      }
      ul.upcoming li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.upcoming li::before { content: '· '; opacity: 0.6; font-style: normal; }

      .privacy-card {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--ochre);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      .privacy-card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      footer {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        padding-top: 1.5rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--taupe);
      }
      footer a { color: var(--taupe); }
      footer a:hover { color: var(--ink); }

      code {
        font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
        background: var(--beige);
        padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
        border-radius: 3px;
        font-size: 0.88em;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header class="hero">
        <h1>Folio</h1>
        <p class="tagline">Restraint → creative flow. Anti-slop infrastructure for children's literature.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a href="/" class="cta primary">Open the editor →</a>
          <a href="/paste" class="cta secondary">Paste-and-analyze</a>
          <a href="/guide" class="cta secondary">How to read the analysis</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section>
        <p>
          Folio is a local-first studio for writers of read-aloud picture books. It shows how a
          manuscript is built — the words a child encounters, the sounds they hear, and the rhythm
          an adult reads aloud — without turning those ingredients into a quality score.
        </p>
        <p>
          The engine measures. It does not author. Folio will never generate manuscript text or
          illustrations on your behalf. The thesis: when the boring legibility work becomes legible
          in the background, creative flow has more room.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who it's for</h2>
        <ul class="audience">
          <li>
            <strong>Picture-book authors</strong>
            Compose one facing spread at a time while the Draft, Listen, and Language lenses reveal
            pacing, vocabulary, rhyme, rhythm, sentence shape, and phoneme structure. The editor MVP
            is centered on board and picture books for ages 0–7; the engine still accepts longer work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Speech-language pathologists</strong>
            The phoneme-acquisition norms in the engine come from <em>Crowe &amp; McLeod (2020), AJSLP</em> —
            the same research base SLPs already use clinically. Select any phoneme in Language to
            highlight every word containing it across the whole manuscript. Useful for evaluating
            whether a candidate text fits a client's current phoneme inventory, or for designing
            intervention materials with controlled sound load.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What's in the editor</h2>
        <ul class="features">
          <li>
            <strong>Facing-spread carousel</strong>
            <span>Write one two-page spread at a time, with independent text and illustration placement on each page. The book-shape strip keeps all 16 spreads visible and shows relative language density.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Rich text</strong>
            <span>Bold, italic, underline, strikethrough via Lexical. Floating toolbar on selection. Markdown shortcuts as you type (<code>**bold**</code>, <code>*italic*</code>, <code>~~strike~~</code>). Soft hyphen and non-breaking space via keyboard.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Draft lens</strong>
            <span>A few evidence-backed reflections about changes in density, vocabulary, sound, and flow. Reflections can take you directly to the affected spread.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Listen and Language lenses</strong>
            <span>Rehearse rhyme, meter, and line shape; then inspect familiar and reach vocabulary, sentence types, pronunciation provenance, and the manuscript's clickable phoneme palette.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>In-context highlighting</strong>
            <span>The writing canvas stays visually clean by default. Select a phoneme in Language to temporarily highlight every word that carries it, using the CSS Custom Highlight API with no DOM mutation or caret disruption.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Local-first manuscript tools</strong>
            <span>Lossless rich-text autosave, multiple local manuscripts, blank structural templates, read-only authored/public-domain examples, per-page composition, and export to plain text, Markdown, or print/PDF.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your privacy</h2>
        <div class="privacy-card">
          <p>
            Folio runs entirely in your browser. Your manuscript content never leaves your device — no
            server roundtrip, no account, no analytics about what you write.
          </p>
          <p>
            Your draft autosaves to this browser's local storage and persists across page reloads. The
            Clear removes it. Anonymous page-view counts are recorded via
            <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy-focused-web-analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plausible</a> —
            cookieless, no personal identifiers, no cross-site tracking.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What's coming</h2>
        <ul class="upcoming">
          <li>Selection-scoped reflections and richer evidence navigation</li>
          <li>Separating reach words into rich literary vocabulary vs. genuinely rare words</li>
          <li>Dialogic-reading prompt suggestions</li>
          <li>Per-client phoneme acquisition profiles for SLP workflows</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer>
        Folio is built by <a href="https://harmonic-systems.org">Harmonic Systems</a>.
        Open source on
        <a href="https://github.com/harmonicsystems/folio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
